.TH INSTALL.SH 1 "July 7, 2025" "1.8.0" "blockman Installer Manual"

.SH NAME
install.sh \- installer and packager for the blockman script

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./install.sh
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B install.sh
is a utility script to manage the installation, uninstallation, and packaging of the
.BR blockman (1)
script. It can perform system-wide installations for all users (requiring root privileges) or user-local installations that do not require special permissions.

It is also capable of generating the necessary files to build standard RPM and DEB packages, including a basic Makefile to streamline the process.

.SH COMMANDS
The script operates based on a single command passed as the first argument.
.TP
.B install
Installs the
.B blockman
script and its corresponding shell completion files. By default, this performs a system-wide installation.
.RS
.TP
\fB--user\fR
When used with the \fBinstall\fR command, performs a user-local installation into the user's home directory (e.g., \fI$HOME/.local/bin\fR). This does not require root privileges.
.RE
.TP
.B uninstall
Removes all files created during the installation process.
.RS
.TP
\fB--user\fR
When used with the \fBuninstall\fR command, removes files from a user-local installation.
.RE
.TP
.B package
Generates a source tarball (\fI.tar.gz\fR) of the
.B blockman
script and creates a \fIpackaging/\fR directory containing the necessary metadata to build RPM (\fI.spec\fR) and DEB (\fIcontrol\fR) packages. It also generates a \fIMakefile\fR.
.TP
.B help
Displays a brief usage message and exits. This is the default command if none is provided.

.SH INSTALLATION PROCESS
.SS System-wide Installation
When run as root without the \fB--user\fR flag, the script will:
.IP \(bu 2
Copy \fBblockman.sh\fR to \fI/usr/local/bin/blockman\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Create a default configuration file at \fI/etc/default/blockman\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Install shell completion files to their respective system-wide directories (e.g., \fI/etc/bash_completion.d/\fR) for all detected shells.

.SS User-local Installation
When run with the \fB--user\fR flag, the script will:
.IP \(bu 2
Copy \fBblockman.sh\fR to \fI$HOME/.local/bin/blockman\fR. The user must ensure this directory is in their \fB$PATH\fB.
.IP \(bu 2
Install shell completion files to user-specific directories (e.g., \fI$HOME/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/\fR).

.SH FILES
.TP
\fI./blockman.sh\fR
The script that this installer manages. Must be in the same directory.
.TP
\fI./Makefile\fR
Generated by the \fBpackage\fR command to provide standard build targets.
.TP
\fI./packaging/\fR
Directory created by the \fBpackage\fR command to hold packaging metadata.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR blockman (1),
.BR make (1)
